(thirdQuint)The Feasibility and Advantages of Tubeless Uniportal Video-assisted Thoracoscopic Surgery in Total Thymectomy.

 This study is a prospective cohort study.

The main study content is the feasibility and advantages of tubeless uniportal video-assisted thoracoscopic surgery in total thymectomy,divided into exposed and non-exposed groups.

Communicating with the surgeon and patients who meet the inclusion criteria, decide whether to enter the exposed or non-exposed group.

Exposed group with tubeless uniportal video-assisted thoracoscopic surgery in total thymectomy , non-exposed group with uniportal video-assisted thoracoscopic surgery in total thymectomy.

By collecting personal information of two groups of patients and the corresponding observation indicators to analyze whether the treatment of thymoma with tubeless uniportal video-assisted thoracoscopic thymectomy is more beneficial than the conventional uniportal video-assisted thoracoscope, and it is safe and feasible.

